This file is an interim notice pending a lawyer-reviewed `LICENSE` per
[`docs/mothership/21-ip-protection-strategy.md §2.1`](docs/mothership/21-ip-protection-strategy.md)
(🜩 lawyer-review item, tracked at `21 §7`). The interim notice asserts
the operator's intent ("never publish under a permissive licence without
explicit decision") and is intentionally restrictive — every legitimate
use case for this repository today (operator development, AI-agent CI
runs, Vercel deployment) operates under that intent.

For the Site repo entity (Lumivara People Advisory marketing site), the
post-assignment licence at handover is `Proprietary — Lumivara People
Advisory` per `21 §3.3` (the SOW assigns site code to the client at
engagement completion). For the Pipeline repo entity (Lumivara Forge
operator framework), the licence remains `All Rights Reserved` to the
operator forever; that artefact set is the practice's competitive moat
per `21 §1` row A and is technically protected by Pattern C's two-repo
trust model.

Third-party dependencies retain their own licences (MIT / Apache 2.0 for
Next.js, Tailwind, shadcn, Base UI React, etc., bundled in
`node_modules/`). This notice covers original work in this repository
only.

